  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Burkina Faso Health Service Reinforcement Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Increase the percentage of children aged 6-23 months with a minimum acceptable diet in target regions from 17.5% to 30%. Increase the number of exclusively breastfed infants age 0-5months from 48% to 60% in targeted regions. Increase the coverage of children age 6-59 months receiving Vitamin A supplementation from 76.1% to 95% in the targeted regions. Increase the percent of women receiving iron and folic acid supplementation for 90 days or more during pregnancy.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Power of Nutrition is contributing $10m into a $30m investment in nutrition in Burkina Faso, which is bringing essential health, nutrition and population services to 5 million women and children by 2023. The programme will primarily focus on scaling up high impact nutrition services using a result-based approach to ensure quality, strengthen data and data systems to enable better tracking of need, coverage of services and progress against indicators, support multisectoral coordination to improve leadership across key government ministries. This $30m programme is part of a wider maternal and child health programme totaling $110m in Burkina Faso.</narrative>
  </description>
